# The gitops image build (bitswan-gitops/Dockerfile) uses the repo root as its
# build context so it can compile the automation-server from source. Keep that
# context lean: only bitswan-gitops/ and bitswan-automation-server/ are needed.
.git
**/node_modules
# …but keep the committed `node_modules -> /deps/node_modules` SYMLINKS that
# ship with the example/business-process templates. They're 18-byte symlinks
# (not real dependency trees), and the scaffolded frontend's live-dev Vite
# server resolves its deps through them — dropping them 500s every new BP.
!bitswan-gitops/examples/**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.vite
**/*.log
bitswan-workspace-dashboard
bitswan-coding-agent
automation-operation-center
